uncc.objects

Class HourRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • uncc.objects.HSQLDatabaseObject
      • uncc.objects.HourRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class HourRange
extends HSQLDatabaseObject
    Object that holds information about the hours in a day that a uncc.objects.Tutor object is available for tutoring, as stored by a uncc.objects.Timesheet object.

    June 17th, 2015

    • Constructor Detail

      • HourRange

        public HourRange(java.lang.Float startTime,
                 java.lang.Float endTime)
          throws javax.management.BadAttributeValueExpException
        Constructor for the HourRange object. If startTime is greater than endTime, then the parameters are switched. A timeSpan of 0.0 (ergo, an HourRange where HourRange.getStartTime() == HourRange.getEndTime()) is permitted.
        Parameters:
        startTime - The hour this HourRange starts from. A positive float strictly less than HOURS_IN_DAY.
        endTime - The hour this HourRange ends at. A positive float strictly less than HOURS_IN_DAY.
        Throws:
        javax.management.BadAttributeValueExpException - If either startTime or endTime is negative, or greater than HOURS_IN_DAY.
